{"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "schema", "document", "Document"], "kwargs": {"page_content": "If $j\\in B$ is one transaction that was included in the block, then we define $g_j$ as the amount of gas that was used by that transaction, and $p_j$ as the price that was paid by the user per unit of gas for that transaction. We define $\\mu$ as the operational cost per unit of gas to the miner for including a given transaction, *i.e.* how much it costs them to include a transaction with a certain amount of gas on the block, vs not including it.\n\nThe utility function for myopic miners under a first price auction mechanism is then,\n$$u_m=\\sum_{j\\in B\\in M}(p_j-\\mu)\\cdot g_j$$\n\nIt is then clear that **the miner's utility is maximized by maximizing the total network revenue: $TNR=\\sum_{j\\in B\\in M}\\,p_j\\cdot g_j$**, and it can be assumed that a rational miner will only include transactions for which $p_j\\ge \\mu$.", "metadata": {}}}